---
import PolicyLayout from "../layouts/PolicyLayout.astro";

const title = "Cookie Policy";
const description = "The cookie policy for Accessible Community.";
---

<PolicyLayout {title} {description}>
<p>Last updated: <time datetime="2024-01-15">15 June 2025</time></p>
  <h2 class="privacy-policy-heading">Plain Language Summary</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>This is a placeholder cookie policy for development purposes.</strong>
    This summary covers the key points but is not the legally binding agreement.
    All content after this summary is the legal cookie policy.
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>This website uses cookies to improve your experience</li>
    <li>Cookies help us understand how you use our site</li>
    <li>Some cookies are essential for the site to work properly</li>
    <li>You can control cookies through your browser settings</li>
    <li>We don't sell cookie data to third parties</li>
    <li>
      Email <a href="mailto:placeholder@example.com">placeholder@example.com</a> with
      questions about cookies
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="privacy-policy-heading">Introduction</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>This is a placeholder cookie policy for development purposes.</strong>
    This Cookie Policy explains how Accessible Community ("us", "we", or "our")
    uses cookies and similar technologies when you visit our website.
  </p>

  <h2 class="privacy-policy-heading">What Are Cookies?</h2>
  <p>
    Cookies are small text files that are placed on your computer or mobile device
    when you visit a website. They help us recognize your browser and provide
    information to improve your experience.
  </p>

  <h2 class="privacy-policy-heading">How We Use Cookies</h2>
  <p>We use cookies for several reasons:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Essential site functions like user authentication</li>
    <li>Performance and analytics to understand site usage</li>
    <li>User experience improvements</li>
    <li>Security features</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="privacy-policy-heading">Types of Cookies We Use</h2>
  <h3 class="privacy-policy-heading">Essential Cookies</h3>
  <p>
    These cookies are necessary for our website to function properly. You cannot
    opt out of these cookies as they are essential for providing our services.
  </p>

  <h3 class="privacy-policy-heading">Performance Cookies</h3>
  <p>
    These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our website by
    collecting anonymous information about pages visited and time spent on pages.
  </p>

  <h2 class="privacy-policy-heading">Managing Your Cookie Preferences</h2>
  <p>
    You can control cookies through your browser settings. Most browsers allow you to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>View cookies stored on your device</li>
    <li>Delete existing cookies</li>
    <li>Block cookies from being set</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Please note that blocking essential cookies may affect your ability to use our services.
  </p>

  <h2 class="privacy-policy-heading">Contact Us</h2>
  <p>
    <a href="mailto:placeholder@example.com">placeholder@example.com</a>
  </p>

  <h2 class="privacy-policy-heading">Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Cookie Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any
    changes by posting the new policy on our website and updating the "Last updated"
    date at the top of this policy.
  </p>
</PolicyLayout>